 {"id":"frankenredis-5h0q","title":"Report real CPU time in INFO cpu section via /proc/self/stat","description":"# Report real CPU time in INFO cpu section\n\n## What\nINFO cpu section reports used_cpu_sys:0.000000 and used_cpu_user:0.000000. On Linux, real values can be read from /proc/self/stat.\n\n## Implementation\nAdd a helper function to fr-command:\n```rust\nfn read_cpu_times() -> (f64, f64) {\n    // Read /proc/self/stat, parse fields 14 (utime) and 15 (stime)\n    // Convert from clock ticks to seconds (divide by sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK), typically 100)\n    // Return (user_seconds, sys_seconds)\n    // On parse failure, return (0.0, 0.0)\n}\n```\n\nUse it in the INFO cpu section.\n\n## Platform considerations\n- /proc/self/stat is Linux-only. On other platforms, return 0.0 (fallback).\n- The libc crate is already a dependency (used by mio), so sysconf is available.\n- Actually, since we forbid unsafe, we should just hardcode CLK_TCK=100 (standard on Linux) or read from /proc/self/status which has a friendlier format.\n\n## Alternative: use std::time::Instant\nTrack cumulative user-space time via Instant measurements. Less accurate but portable.\n\n## Priority\nLOW — cosmetic improvement. Monitoring tools can function without CPU metrics.\n\n## Files to modify\n- crates/fr-command/src/lib.rs (info() CPU section)","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-03T00:21:21.036969669Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-05T23:44:33.609307948Z","closed_at":"2026-04-05T23:44:33.608904835Z","close_reason":"Implementation already present in tracked tree; verified by source inspection and targeted unit test coverage exists","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
