 {"id":"frankenredis-yc3","title":"Implement lexical scoping / upvalue capture in Lua evaluator","description":"## Problem\n\nfr-command/src/lua_eval.rs line 2274: When calling a LuaValue::Function, a completely fresh environment is created (Env::new()). This means closures cannot access variables from their defining scope.\n\nExample that breaks:\n  local x = 10\n  local f = function() return x end\n  return f()  -- returns nil, should return 10\n\nThis is a FUNDAMENTAL semantic bug that silently breaks any Lua code using closures, callbacks, or higher-order functions.\n\n## How Real Lua Does It\n\nLua 5.1 uses upvalue capture: when a function is created, it captures references to local variables in enclosing scopes. These captured variables (upvalues) travel with the function closure.\n\n## Implementation Options\n\n### Option A: Environment Chain (simpler)\nWhen creating a LuaValue::Function, snapshot the current environment as a parent chain. When the function is called, create a new env with the captured parent as the lookup fallback.\n\nData model change:\n- LuaValue::Function currently stores (name, body_statements)\n- Change to store (name, body_statements, captured_env: Option<Env>)\n- In Env::get(), if local lookup fails, walk the captured_env chain\n\n### Option B: Explicit Upvalue Tracking (more correct)\nTrack which variables are referenced by the function body. Only capture those specific bindings. More memory-efficient but harder to implement.\n\n## Recommendation\n\nOption A is much simpler and sufficient for Redis Lua scripts (which are typically not deeply nested). The performance cost is minimal since Env is just a HashMap.\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n- crates/fr-command/src/lua_eval.rs: LuaValue::Function variant, Env struct, call_function, function definition handling\n\n## Testing\n\n- Test: local variable access from closure\n- Test: nested closures (closure inside closure)\n- Test: closure over loop variable\n- Test: multiple closures sharing same upvalue\n- Test: redis.call inside a closure","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:08:10.287677089Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T05:22:00.978183370Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T05:22:00.977708791Z","close_reason":"Implemented upvalue capture via captured_env on LuaFunc. Functions now snapshot the lexical scope at definition time and restore it on call, enabling closures.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"frankenredis-yc3","depends_on_id":"frankenredis-7vn","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:08:23.998554629Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
